HEADWORD: Abraid
<hw>A*braid"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>abraiden</ets>, to awake, draw (a sword), AS.
<ets>⟦amac⟧bredgan</ets> to shake, draw; pref. <ets>⟦amac⟧-</ets> (cf.
Goth. <ets>us-</ets>, Ger. <ets>er-</ets>, orig. meaning <ets>out</ets>)
+ <ets>bregdan</ets> to shake, throw. See <er>Braid</er>.]</ety> <def>To
awake; to arouse; to stir or start up; also, to shout out.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
